         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanic Garden, ¶ 22 May 1872. ¶  ¶ With last month's mail, esteemed Sir, I sent you a series of specimens of  ¶ Scleranthus ¶  species, and now I take the liberty of additionally offering a...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">72.05.22a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Ludwig Reichenbach</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Dörflersamlingen, Universitetsbiblioteket, Uppsala.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation: '23 Apr. 73', presumably the date of reply (letter not found). A comparison of the handwriting of Ludwig Reichenbach (1793-1879) and that of his son, Heinrich Gottlieb Reichenbach (1824-89), shows that this annotation was written by the father.</p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">Melbourne im bot. </seg>Garten,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">22/5/72.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mit letzter Monatspost sandte ich Ihnen, sehr verehrter Herr, eine Reihe Exemplare von Scleranthus Arten, und nun erlaube ich mir noch nachträglich den <name key="Scleranthus%20biflorus">Scleranthus biflorus</name> auch von Neu Seeland an zubieten. Wie ich vor fast 20 Jahren das genus <name key="Mniarum">Mniarum</name> einzog und die typische species <name key="Scleranthus%20mniarum">Scleranthus mniarum</name> nannte, hatte ich noch nicht die Flora Novo-Zelandica des jüngern Hooker erhalten.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sollten sich noch andere Arten hiernach finden, u solche in meinen Besitz kommen, so werde ich nicht verfehlen Ihnen solche vorzulegen.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mit besonderer Verehrung</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Botanic Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22 May 1872.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With last month's mail, esteemed Sir, I sent you a series of specimens of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Scleranthus</seg> species, and now I take the liberty of additionally offering also <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Scleranthus%20biflorus">Scleranthus biflorus</name>
               </seg> from New Zealand. When, nearly 20 years ago, I suppressed the genus <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Mniarum">Mniarum</name>
               </seg> and called the typical species <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Scleranthus%20mniarum">Scleranthus mniarum</name>
               </seg>,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">mniaroides</seg>? M suppressed <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Mniarum">Mniarum</name>
                     </seg> in his treatment of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Scleranthus mniaroides </seg>
                     <seg style="">in</seg> B62.03.03, p. 215, but had given the name '<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Scleranthus mniaroides</seg> Ferd Mueller collect.' for what he described as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Mniarum">Mniarum</name> singuliflorum</seg> in B54.13.06, pp. 13-14, stating 'by the constantly 5-cleft calyx of this kind <name key="Mniarum">Mniarum</name> becomes so closely allied to Scleranthus, that hardly any objection can be raised against the conjunction of the two genera'.</p>
               </note> I had not yet received the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Flora Novo-Zelandica</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1853-5), vol. 1, p. 74, suppressed <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Mniarum">Mniarum</name>
                     </seg> in the treatment of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Scleranthus%20biflorus">Scleranthus biflorus</name>, </seg>stating 'I see no ground upon which to separate [<name key="Mniarum">Mniarum</name>] from Scleranthus'.</p>
               </note> of the younger Hooker.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Should still other species be found later on and come into my possession, I shall not fail to place them before you.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">With particular veneration</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Mniarum">Mniarum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Scleranthus%20biflorus">Scleranthus biflorus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Scleranthus%20mniarum">Scleranthus mniarum</name>
            </p>
         </div>
